Typhinellus jacolombi
varies in shell colour, ranging from completely white with darker brown subsutural area ( paratype RH) to completely light brown ( paratype RH) (
Fig. 2 d–f
). The protoconch ( paratype JC) is small and rounded (
Fig. 2 k
) and the total shell length may attain 28.7 mm (
Fig. 2 d–f
).
